  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In source code vulnerability detection, (Nguyen et al. 2022b) developed an approach called ReGVD.",
    "This method first constructs the source code as a graph structure and initializes the node features using a pre-trained programming language model.",
    "Furthermore, the feature representation is enhanced by residual connections in a graph neural network and the final graph embedding is generated using hybrid graph-level summation pooling and maximum pooling.",
    "This approach improves the efficiency and flexibility of source code vulnerability detection.",
    "In short, these approaches demonstrate the strong potential of graph pooling techniques in the field of cybersecurity to effectively handle complex graph-structured data from which valuable information can be mined for security threat detection and defense."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In source code vulnerability detection, (Nguyen et al. 2022b) developed an approach called ReGVD."
  ]
}